PN,31302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1775851553
OL,3,CHow the Artemis crew will splash down
OL,4,Con Earth
OL,6,FTheir journey is part of Nasa's long-
OL,7,Fterm plan to return humans to the
OL,8,Fsurface of the Moon ` part of its
OL,9,Fbroader mission to put feet on the
OL,10,Fground of Mars.
OL,12,FReturning to Earth is seen as one of
OL,13,Fthe most difficult tasks of any
OL,14,Fspacecraft.
OL,16,FThe extreme heat and turbulence
OL,17,Fgenerated by re-entering the
OL,18,Fatmosphere presents a significant
OL,19,Fengineering challenge and is seen as
OL,20,Fone of the most dangerous parts of the
OL,21,Ftrip.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
