PN,31306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1775851553
OL,3,CHow the Artemis crew will splash down
OL,4,Con Earth
OL,6,FWith final preparations complete, the
OL,7,Fcapsule will begin re-entering the
OL,8,Fatmosphere at 23,864 mph, roughly 13
OL,9,Fminutes before it's due to hit the
OL,10,Focean.
OL,12,FAs Orion descends through about
OL,13,F400,000 feet, the spacecraft will
OL,14,Fenter a planned sixminute
OL,15,Fcommunications blackout, as plasma
OL,16,Fforms around the capsule during peak
OL,17,Fheating.
OL,19,FThe crew are expected to experience
OL,20,Fclose to 4G (four times Earth's
OL,21,Fgravity) during this time.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
