PN,31307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1775851553
OL,3,CHow the Artemis crew will splash down
OL,4,Con Earth
OL,6,FOnce through the atmosphere, the
OL,7,Fcapsule's parachutes will deploy,
OL,8,Fslowing them down before eventually
OL,9,Fcolliding with the ocean at around
OL,10,F8.07pm local time off the coast of San
OL,11,FDiego.
OL,13,FAfter that, the crew will remain in
OL,14,Fthe capsule while the parachutes
OL,15,Fdetach.
OL,17,FWithin two hours, US Navy helicopters
OL,18,Fwill recover the crew and fly them to
OL,19,Fthe nearby USS John P. Murtha.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
